ed.\\\" It seems I don't need to worry further for now.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"No extra dependency or Docker service is needed: Vert.x Web Client can be meaningfully exercised against an in-process Vert.x HTTP server. However, Vert.x 5.0.1 resolves Netty 4.2.2.Final, and the existing 5.0.0 test scaffold already documents Java 25 native-run system properties for Netty 4.2.x; the same native runtime setup should apply to 5.0.1.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"For native-image runtime tests on JDK 25/current-defaults, configure the test Gradle `nativeTest` runtime args for Vert.x 5.0.1 to include `-Dsun.misc.unsafe.memory.access=allow` and `-Dio.netty.tryReflectionSetAccessible=true`. Meaningful coverage can use a local `Vertx.createHttpServer()` and `WebClient` against `127.0.0.1`; no external HTTP service is required.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"If tests intentionally cover optional OAuth2-specific Web Client APIs, `io.vertx:vertx-auth-oauth2:5.0.1` may be needed, but the core Web Client usage and existing coverage patterns do not require it.\",\n    \"Local Gradle and Native Image verification remain authoritative for whether the Netty Java 25 runtime flags fully address the observed native-run failure.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_006e49193cb5e374016a3e94d3ece481908eb95b7bf6c8f95d\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 855, "output": 830, "cacheRead": 32768, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 34453, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782486214726, "responseId": "resp_006e49193cb5e374016a3e94c78d288190910406a7bba8001c"}}
